/*
========================================================
DOWNLOAD MANAGER – COMPLETE THEORY (ANDROID)
========================================================

--------------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS DownloadManager ?
--------------------------------------------------------
• DownloadManager is an ANDROID SYSTEM SERVICE
• Provided by Android OS
• Used to download files in background
• Works even if app is closed or killed
• Android system performs the actual download

IMPORTANT:
Your app DOES NOT download the file.
Android OS downloads the file on your behalf.

--------------------------------------------------------
WHY SHOULD WE USE DownloadManager ?
--------------------------------------------------------
Because Android already solves all hard problems:

✔ Background execution
✔ App process death handling
✔ Network changes (Wi-Fi ↔ Mobile)
✔ Retry logic
✔ Battery optimization
✔ System download notifications
✔ Large file handling

Using DownloadManager = Using Android best practices.

--------------------------------------------------------
WHEN SHOULD WE USE DownloadManager ?
--------------------------------------------------------
Use DownloadManager when:

✔ Downloading LARGE files
✔ Download must continue if app is killed
✔ File should be user-visible
✔ Reliability is important
✔ System notification is required

REAL-WORLD USE CASES:
• Image / Video download
• PDF / ZIP download
• Music files
• Reports / invoices
• Offline content

--------------------------------------------------------
IS DownloadManager LEGACY ?
--------------------------------------------------------
❌ NO — DownloadManager is NOT legacy

FACTS:
• Still part of Android SDK
• Actively maintained
• Used internally by Google apps
• Not deprecated

It is STABLE, not obsolete.

--------------------------------------------------------
WHEN SHOULD WE NOT USE DownloadManager ?
--------------------------------------------------------
❌ Do NOT use DownloadManager for:

• API calls (JSON / XML)
• Uploading files
• Streaming data
• Real-time sync
• Custom authentication headers
• Small network requests

--------------------------------------------------------
WHAT ARE THE ALTERNATIVES ?
--------------------------------------------------------
Depends on use-case (NOT replacements).

--------------------------------------------------------
COMPARISON TABLE
--------------------------------------------------------

| Tool / Feature        | DownloadManager | Service | WorkManager | Retrofit | Flow |
|----------------------|-----------------|---------|-------------|----------|------|
| Runs if app killed   | YES             | NO      | YES         | NO       | NO   |
| Large file support   | BEST            | RISKY   | LIMITED     | MANUAL   | NO   |
| System notification  | AUTO            | MANUAL  | MANUAL      | MANUAL   | NO   |
| Battery optimized    | YES             | NO      | YES         | DEPENDS  | NO   |
| Retry handling       | AUTO            | MANUAL  | AUTO        | MANUAL   | NO   |
| User-visible file    | YES             | NO      | NO          | NO       | NO   |
| Background safe      | YES             | NO      | YES         | NO       | NO   |

--------------------------------------------------------
DOWNLOADMANAGER vs SERVICE
--------------------------------------------------------
SERVICE:
• App-owned
• Easily killed
• Must manage threads
• Background restricted
• Battery unfriendly

DOWNLOADMANAGER:
• System-owned
• Never killed
• Background-safe
• Optimized by OS

RULE:
Never use Service for file downloads.

--------------------------------------------------------
DOWNLOADMANAGER vs WORKMANAGER
--------------------------------------------------------
DownloadManager:
• File downloads
• User-visible
• Immediate execution
• System notifications

WorkManager:
• Background tasks
• App logic
• Deferred execution
• No built-in notifications

They solve DIFFERENT problems.

--------------------------------------------------------
DOWNLOADMANAGER vs RETROFIT / OKHTTP
--------------------------------------------------------
DownloadManager:
• Files
• Background safe
• Automatic retries
• Limited control

Retrofit / OkHttp:
• API calls
• App must be alive
• Full control
• Manual handling

RULE:
APIs → Retrofit
Files → DownloadManager

--------------------------------------------------------
WHERE DOES FLOW FIT ?
--------------------------------------------------------
Flow is NOT a downloader.

• Flow is a reactive data stream
• Used to observe data changes
• Needs Retrofit / DownloadManager underneath

Flow can OBSERVE download status,
but cannot download files itself.

--------------------------------------------------------
ARCHITECTURAL RULE (MUST REMEMBER)
--------------------------------------------------------
API DATA        → Retrofit / OkHttp
FILE DOWNLOAD  → DownloadManager
BACKGROUND JOB → WorkManager
UI STATE       → Flow / LiveData

--------------------------------------------------------
ONE-LINE INTERVIEW ANSWERS
--------------------------------------------------------
Q: Why DownloadManager?
A: Because it is system-managed and background-safe.

Q: Is it deprecated?
A: No, it is stable and recommended.

Q: When not to use?
A: For APIs, uploads, or streaming.

--------------------------------------------------------
FINAL ONE-LINE SUMMARY (MEMORIZE)
--------------------------------------------------------
DownloadManager is the safest,
system-approved way to download files
that must survive app death.
========================================================
*/
